data: "Episode 1" "The vagrant who talks backwards（把话倒着来说的流浪汉）"

Meichen disappears on Jiang Wei's wedding day. Jiang Wei receives a phone call, and searches for her, only to find a wedding veil left on the roadside near the church where the wedding is supposed to be held. He realized that she went off without a trace, and Jiang Wei was heartbroken. Jiang Wei remains heartbroken ever since that day three years ago, and is seen conversing to himself as the episode opens. He now stays in a HDB flat which looks as though he had just came in, even though he moved a year ago. Yang Zhiqing and her mother, Zhang Cuiyan, run a fried beehoon stall at a coffeeshop. Jiang Wei patronises the stall. When he sees his mother, he hides, and did not collect his food. Zhiqing runs after Jiang Wei with the food. Outside the flat, a resident dries his laundry upstairs, Zhiqing tries to move back as the water drops on her spectacles, and falls after bumping Jiang Wei holding on to "Missing" fliers of Meichen. Her spectacles fall off her face. Zhiqing has a paranormal ability to see into other people's inner souls. While she retrieves her spectacles, she sees Jiang Wei morph into a filthy and gloomy vagrant in front of her, talking backwards ("吧事没你?", meaning "Are you OK?" backwards). She concludes that he was running away from reality. The vagrant saves Zhiqing from being crushed by the impact of the body falling from the roof. Before Zhiqing wears back her spectacles, she stole one more look at the vagrant. Police officer Qiu Hanxiang turns up at the scene, and finds shopping coupons from 10 years ago on the female corpse. Coffeeshop tenant Dong-shu and his wife are very strict with their son, Weijian, and sends him to his tuition and piano lessons. As Weijian drags his feet for his lesson, Zhiqing removes her glasses, and sees Weijian with a huge scholar hat being handcuffed and walks with metal balls attached to his feet. She analyses that he is suffering, but has no idea how she can help. Zhiqing delivers food to the mental asylum and sees psychiatrist Xu Wenbin calming an agitated patient down. She tells him about Jiang Wei, and he gathers that Jiang Wei must have a sad past. Meanwhile, Cuiyan wants Jiang Wei to help her find her missing husband but can’t afford his fee. The deceased was later identified to be Huang Lifang, who has been missing for 10 years. The day she went missing, she was on the way to the supermarket to use the coupons. As Lifang’s looks remain unchanged, no one can explain what happened. Hanxiang and Jiang Wei checked for any clues three days before she entered the lift, but were unavailable. Jiang Wei later suspect that Meichen may have disappeared and her age may have been frozen. Dong-sao rushed to the coffeeshop, telling everyone that Weijian went missing as she brought him home. Zhiqing seeks the help of Jiang Wei to find Weijian, after she failed to find him the night before, when Wenbin consoles Zhiqing and tells her that even if she can see other people’s inner world, whatever happens to them has nothing to do with her.

"Episode 2" "A pair of strange eyes（一双古怪的眼睛）"

Five years ago, Zhiqing wakes up to find herself confined in a room of a mental asylum. Wenbin enters the room. As Zhiqing opens her eyes, she became petrified at the first sight of him... Zhiqing and Jiang Wei went to search Weijian. As she sees a student's back who looks like Weijian's, she chases him, only to break her spectacles in a near accident. Zhiqing tells Jiang Wei that she can see other people’s inner worlds and had been sent to a mental asylum before. He presumes she has hallucinations. She surprises him when she describes exactly how he feels. Wenbin takes Zhiqing to get a new pair of spectacles made. She is grateful to him, and remembers how he had helped her when she was in the mental asylum. Cuiyan complains about the noise from upstairs, only to learn that her neighbour is overseas, and fear grips her. Jiang Wei, Zhiqing and Hanxiang check the CCTV footage of the lift on the day Weijian went missing. Weijian walks out of the lift on the 13th floor, whereas another passenger in the CCTV footage of the void deck of the 13th floor, enters the lift but did not meet Weijian. Jiang Wei links the disappearance to Lifang’s case. Zhiqing takes the lift repeatedly, hoping to find clues to Weijian’s disappearance. The neighbours presume she has gone mad again. The lift malfunctions and needs to be repaired. Zhiqing goes missing near the 13th floor as well. Zhiqing enters the 13.5th storey and finds Weijian there. She finds herself in vibrating and extending corridors, and the scenery was as if it was watery. In an open space, she finds a student playing marbles, a lady "playing mahjong", and a man who seems to be "singing in a concert". In order to locate Zhiqing, Jiang Wei, Wenbin and Cuiyan studies the CCTV footage of the lift when Zhiqing disappeared. He concludes that Zhiqing, Weijian and Lifang ended up into another dimension at 13:13 (1.13pm) in the afternoon on the 13th floor, and these disappearances have something to do with the number 13. Meanwhile, Cuiyan hires a priest to conduct rites. The priest is a quack, and Jiang Wei exposes him and chases him away.

"Episode 3" "Welcome to 13-and-a-half floor（欢迎来到十三层楼半）"

Jiang Wei wakes up in a hospital, and the first thing that came to his mind is a baby which he saved from an abduction case. Worried about her, he dashes out of his ward and gets stopped by Meichen and the nurses. They send him to the ward where the baby was taken care of. Jiang Wei faints after falling from the drain earlier on, while still holding on to the baby in his hands. They would not have been found if water in the drain washes them away. Jiang Wei passes out again. Meichen sees him as a hero in her heart since that day. The episode starts with the lift opening its doors in the 13th floor. Jiang Wei summarized that the number 13 is the clue to saving Zhiqing and Weijian. Jiang Wei calls Hanxiang to say he is going to enter into another dimension. Wenbin remembers that he had once played a song in the guitar for Zhiqing to celebrate he release from hospital. Guessing that the noise Cuiyan had heard was from the other dimension, he tries to use music to lure Zhiqing back. Zhiqing sees the ground at the open space vibrating due to the sound, but she could not be heard back at home. The sound was cut at 1.13pm, when Jiang Wei enters to the 13.5th floor. He runs out when he sees Weijian scooting away, but gets thrown into another reality, at a lobby of a condominium. There, he reunites with Meichen. Zhiqing sees Jiang Wei slowly moving to "Meichen's apartment", and suddenly appears, trying to get him out. All she can see is a dilapidated place, and Jiang Wei seems to be talking and holding to the air. Jiang Wei chases her out. Zhiqing finds Weijian facing the television, seemingly "playing an Xbox game", and she does not see the "fridge" he points out. Zhiqing tries to make Jiang Wei wake up from his dream, but gets chased out again, even though Meichen does not answer her parents' birthday dates. She does so the second time, telling him to close his eyes as he hugs Meichen. Meichen reappears after he closed his eyes for the first time. Meichen and everything dissolves for the second time, and he realized that everything is a figment of imagination when he is unable to find her. In this dimension, time is frozen and people are stuck in their own fantasies. Jiang Wei and Zhiqing runs down the stairs and finds themselves reappearing back at the top of the stairs. No one resides there in this storey. Zhiqing She realizes that when she chased after Weijian after entering the dimension, she tumbled and drops her glasses, and therefore does not have any illusions due to the function of her glasses, And only she can see the truth. After a few hours, they hear Wenbin's music and stomp their feet to let the others know they are there. The music cuts again. As they went back to the lifts, they found the other slipper Lifang wore when she fell down, and thus the place where they could escape from the dimension.

Cuiyan hides Zhiqing from by the police. Four police officers eventually find them hiding amongst the boxes and two of them carries Zhiqing away. As Zhiqing opens her eyes, she sees her mother morph back into the same clown figure, letting go of the two other police officers away and standing there, sobbing away. Jiang Wei and Zhiqing thought of what could had happened before Liang Lifang fell down from this dimension. She could have entered into an illusion for 10 years, before waking up to find herself trapped in the reality. Anxiety gripped her, and she jumped off the building when she could hold it no longer. Jiang Wei sends a message to Hanxiang using Zhiqing's mobile phone and dropping it down. Hanxiang gets the message and gets the help of some officers to erect an air mattress to save Jiang Wei. With no more chips or water left, Jiang Wei sees Meichen on the other side, giving her hand to him, but gets pulled back by Zhiqing. He later decides to jump down from the building, rather than die in the dimension, though Zhiqing holds him back so that he could continue to find Meichen. Two days later Wenbin continues to use his guitar to communicate with Zhiqing, but only Weijian made it back. His restless parents, who were traumatised by his disappearance, tells him that they would not force him to score the best grades. He recounts to Wenbin about his imagination, and how he gets rescued by Zhiqing. Wenbin reveals to Jiang Wei about Zhiqing's paranormal ability to see other people's inner souls. The first person she sees was her mother in a purple dress with yellow polka-dots; white circles around her eyes and messy hair, who later declines wearing these. As she walks out of the house, she was surrounded by people of all sorts, from acrobats to traditional costume dressers and even invisible men. At first, she was fascinated but later became terrified. As she dashes to the coffeeshop, she became more and more frightened by the things she sees and hides behind her mother, who was weeping away. Therefore, other people find her weird as she became mentally ill, and was admitted to the mental hospital. Wenbin studied her case and realised her ability is a form of extra-sensory perception. Wenbin then bought her a pair of glasses which helps Zhiqing to block out the visions she sees. As she puts off her glasses, she immediately puts them on again. Wenbin thus suggests her to close her eyes when she is not wearing the glasses. Jiang Wei and Wenbin made a pact to enter the 13.5th floor again. As they returned to the scene, Zhiqing's spectacles dropped close to Jiang Wei and realises that she is going to land away from the mattress. Hanxiang gets his men to move the mattress where Zhiqing would fall. Zhiqing jumps off the building and finally lands on the mattress, saddened that she could not help the other three trapped people who ignores her, back to reality. Jiang Wei makes Zhiqing understand that she has a special gift and should not be afraid of it. In turn, she promises to help him find Meichen. Wenbin later tells Zhiqing that her mother tries not to speak ill of other people and make them happy, but behind these, she is still in sorrow. Meanwhile, Hanxiang takes Jiang Wei home, but the latter lacks the courage to see his family, while his father, Jiang Yu, is livid as he has been neglecting them the past three years.

table-1111-392.caption: Quotes
data: Fear and weakness live inside us, and sometimes they win.（恐惧和软弱是与生俱来，有些时候他们还战胜我们。）
A question that sometimes drives me hazy, am I or the others crazy? （有时我会迷惑，是我疯了；还是别人疯了？）
It's hard to find an enemy who has outposts in your head. （对于洞悉你想法的对手，你是难以匹敌的。）
The defects and faults in the mind are like wounds in the body. After all imaginable care has been taken to heal them up, still there will be a scar left behind. （灵性的缺失，犹如肉体的创伤，即使在用尽医疗方法治愈，还是会留下疤痕。）
The quality, not the longevity, of one's life is what is important. （重要的是，人的一生要活得有素质，而不是活得长久。）
Wealth is like sea-water; the more we drink, the thirstier we become; and the same is true of fame.（财富就像海水，饮得越多，渴得越厉害；名望实际上也是如此。）
Only love can unlock the mystery of immortality. （唯有爱能解开不死之谜。）
In the end, it's not the years in your life that count. It's the life in your years.（到头来，人们不会在意你活了多少岁，而是你曾经如何生活。）
The dream does not conceal anything, we simply do not understand its language.（梦并没有对我们隐瞒什么，只是我们不理解他的语言罢了。）
All is riddle, and the key to a riddle..., is another riddle.（万物皆谜，解谜之道...是另一个谜。）
不知周之梦为蝴蝶与？蝴蝶之梦为周与？(Did Zhuang Zhou dream that he was a butterfly, or a butterfly dreaming that it was Zhuang Zhou?)
The torture of a bad conscience is the hell of a living soul.（坏人一旦恢复良知，其内心所受的折磨，将使之感到有如身陷地狱。）
There is no disguise which can hide love for long where it exists, or simulate it where it does not.（爱情发生了，你是无法长久假装若无其事，但如果没有发生，也不可能装模作样。）
I'm happy, because l have love.（我幸福，因为我有爱。）
Where a man may happen to turn, whatever a man may undertake, he will always end up by returning to the path which nature has marked out for him.（一个人的行为偶尔会转变，或是出人意表地承担一些什么，但他最终总会变回老样子，因为本性难移。）
Falling into disfavor and jealousy have turned gods into degenerates.（因失宠而嫉妒，曾使天使坠落。）
I have loved to the point of madness, that which is called madness, that which to me, is the only sensible way to love.（我曾经爱至被人们视我为疯狂的境地，对于我来说，那可是爱的不二法门。）
众里寻他千百度，蓦然回首，那人却在灯火阑珊处。(I search for her everywhere. Fortuitously I turn around; And there she is standing where the light is dim.)
There is no such thing as coincidence, everything happens for a reason. （事出皆有因，绝非巧合。）
Every end is a new beginning.（每一个结局是一个新的起点。）

data: Jane handles the case of a man whose wife committed suicide after being rejected for a reality TV makeover show. The case pits her against a smooth lawyer and a blunt jury consultant whose criticism of Jane's style makes her believe it's Luke's plan to make her act less like Deb. Parker is thrown by a case of two women fighting over a rat they claim is their mutual reincarnated lover and by the appearance of his son at the firm. Using inspiration from Eddie and Elisa, Parker finally tells the two women to stop fighting and move on with their lives after revealing that Ted played them for fools. Stacy gets Teri to help her open her "pakery." Teri hires real help and her "pakery" opens.

Owen soon reveals a small truth that the lawyer did that made the people on trial plead the fifth, which Jane is encouraged to use. When a man claims to have invented the "pake" and shows up with a patent, Stacy must locate Nikki to save her store. She is also upset to find that Jane is planning to move out to be with Owen. Grayson saves Stacy by having a "pake-off" in a courtoom, which exposes Mr. Piers' scam and gives her the patent. Luke is thrown when Kim reveals the reason they cannot date.

Jane and Grayson team up to take the case of a man whose wife, an old friend of Deb's refuses to have life-saving surgery when a brain tumor makes her smarter. Kim defends a singer after a fan claims one of her songs encouraged an attack on the singer's ex-boyfriend. Luke learns Kim's secret. As Jane's wedding day approaches, Grayson decides to reveal his true feelings for her. Meanwhile, in Heaven, the spirit of the real Jane goes to Fred to get her old life back. At Jane and Owen's wedding, Kim tells Parker that she's pregnant with his child. After confessing his feelings for Jane, Grayson and her kiss, but they are caught by Owen, who dies of a heart attack. Unknowing to Jane/Deb is that the spirit of the real Jane Bingum appears to have entered into Owen's body.
